<DOC><DOCNO> AP880608-0140 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-08-88 1258EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--ArianeLaunch     06-08 0148</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Ariane Launch,0150</SECOND><HEAD>Ariane Launch Scheduled For June 15</HEAD><DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The demonstration launch of the Ariane-4 rocketthat was delayed by mechanical and computer problems has beenrescheduled for June 15, officials announced Wednesday.   A statement released by Arianespace, the commercial arm of theEuropean Space Agency, said repairs on the rocket were completed atthe launch site in Kourou, French Guiana.   The repair work between the payload and launcher sections of therocket involved rewiring an adapter. A new on-board computer wasfitted in the vehicle equipment bay and tested, the statement said.   Ariane-4, designed to serve as the space agency's new workhorse,will carry three satellites into orbit _ a European weathersatellite, and two telecommunications satellites, including one forthe American company Pan American Satellite.   The launch also is designed as a demonstration for futurecustomers of the rocket's versatility and power.</TEXT></DOC>